From 5469738ca5cdb2c37e8c71a7228d8823cf511b72 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Matthew Feickert <matthew.feickert@cern.ch>
Date: Tue, 17 Feb 2026 23:43:50 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] fix: Migrate Cython 2 patterns to Cython 3 compatibility
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Cython 3.x removed or changed several behaviors from Cython 2:

1. cpdef for module-level variables (cram.pyx):
   cpdef cannot declare module-level variables in Cython 3. Changed
   `cpdef dict C_IJ` and `cpdef list C_NUCS` to `cdef`, since the
   Python-accessible names IJ and NUCS are assigned separately.

2. Python 2 `long` builtin removed (rxname.pyx, particle.pyx,
   nucname.pyx, stlcontainers.pyx):
   In Python 3, `long` is not a builtin type — `int` covers all
   integer sizes. Replaced `long(x)` casts with direct variable or
   `int(x)`, and removed all `isinstance(x, long)` branches that are
   unreachable in Python 3 (int already handles all integers).

3. C++ reference type assignment (cpp_material.pxd, enrichment.pyx,
   material_library.pyx):
   Cython 3 strictly distinguishes `T &` (reference) from `T` (value).
   Assigning `Material *` dereference (returning `Material &`) to a
   `Material` value field now requires an explicit copy constructor
   call. Added `Material(Material &)` copy constructor declaration to
   cpp_material.pxd, and updated enrichment.pyx and material_library.pyx
   to call `Material(ptr[0])` explicitly for the copy.
---
 pyne/cpp_material.pxd     |  1 +
 pyne/cram.pyx             |  4 +--
 pyne/enrichment.pyx       |  6 ++---
 pyne/material_library.pyx |  2 +-
 pyne/nucname.pyx          | 42 +++++++++++++++---------------
 pyne/particle.pyx         | 18 ++++++-------
 pyne/rxname.pyx           | 18 +++----------
 pyne/stlcontainers.pyx    | 54 +++++++++++++++++++--------------------
 8 files changed, 68 insertions(+), 77 deletions(-)

